		%h5 Welcome, UX collective
		%section
			%p 
				Hi, UX2.0 is a project funded by 
				%a{:href=>"http://www.jisc.ac.uk/whatwedo/programmes/inf11.aspx"} JISC
				(Information Environment Programme 2009-11) 
				to undertake research and development to enhance user experience of 
				digital libraries, through technological developments that are centered on 
				usability inspection and evaluation.
	%article
		%h5 Usability Testing of Digital Library Prototype
		%section
			%p
				:markdown
					We have undertaken usability testing of UX2's Blacklight-based digital library prototype and 
					[published the findings in a report](http://bit.ly/ux2usabilityreport1). The
					test reveals a range of issues uncovered by observing 
					representative users using the prototype at the University of Edinburgh. 
					The findings outlined in the report provide a number of recommendations 
					for changes to the prototype in order to improve the userâ€™s experience.
	%article
		%h5 Last but not Least..
		%section
			%p
				:markdown
					The [AquaBrowser User Experience](https://www.wiki.ed.ac.uk/display/UX2/AquaBrowserUX)
					project has come to an end. We have been busy in the past months undertaking various
					activities: user research for personas, contextual inquiry and finally a bout of usability test,
					assessing Edinburgh University Library users in actions with AquaBrowser. You are welcome to
					check out the [usability test report](http://bit.ly/aquxusabilityreport) and the video below, 
					highlighting the user reaction and behaviour:
			%p
				:markdown
					- [Facet Navigation](http://ux2.nesc.ed.ac.uk:8080/fedora/get/lib:10186/mp4)
					- [Information Seeking](http://ux2.nesc.ed.ac.uk:8080/fedora/get/lib:10187/mp4)
					- [Word Cloud](http://ux2.nesc.ed.ac.uk:8080/fedora/get/lib:10187/mp4)
					
